\b \cf0 Control Flow\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 The program is primarily controlled through the Driver, which initializes the initial main Deck, distributes Card objects to Player and AI, and creates the current Game with the data. PlayingAreaAI and PlayingArea allow for the AI and the Player to take action through clicks for the player and a timer for the AI. Game holds the current Player\'92s data and the AI\'92s data, as well as the center Deck. Player and AI each hold their side Decks, and Decks in turn handle the Car objects they hold.  \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 I/O\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 Input is done through user clicks on the mouse, which the Driver detects. Driver then allows PlayingArea to decide if the click occurred on a Card that can be played, and if possible, that Card is then played. Output is done through the GUI, as the program will update using paint when actions occur that change the display (such as a center reset or card play).\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\b \cf0 UI\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 The UI is relatively straightforward, with the user\'92s cards displayed in a row at the top and the AI\'92s cards displayed on the opposite side at the bottom. The center deck is in the middle of the two. \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

